	<h2 style="margin-bottom:0px;">High S Performance Management</h2>
	<h1 style="text-align:center; margin-top:0px;">Strengths and Weaknesses</h1>
	<br>
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Planning and Goal Setting</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table1">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Understands job thoroughly</li>
					<li>Writes plan carefully </li>
					<li>Defines the goal in terms of manageable components</li>
					<li>Lays out a well-structured, complete plan</li>
					<li>Gets employee involved in planning</li>
					<li>Modifies plan to suit employees strengths and limitations</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>May be more task than concept-oriented</li>
					<li>May not tie plan to business results</li>
					<li>Focuses more on process than result</li>
					<li>Can be too subjective</li>
					<li>May not set ambitious goals</li>
					<li>May over emphasize employee wants and needs in goal setting</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Measuring and Monitoring Progress/Coaching</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table2">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Creates a non-threatening environment</li>
					<li>Provides a positive personal example</li>
					<li>Builds personal relationships</li>
					<li>Helps employee draw own conclusions about progress</li>
					<li>Demonstrates a strong commitment to cooperation</li>
					<li>Involves employee in problem solving</li>
					<li>Coaches to keep work on track</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>May not focus on the big picture</li>
					<li>May not recognize accomplishments enthusiastically</li>
					<li>May overlook potential problems rather than dealing with them early</li>
					<li>Doesn’t encourage creativity and “thinking outside the box”</li>
					<li>May have tendency to jump in and get hands on in dealing with issues</li>
					<li>May fail to seek closure, particularly if they sense these is underlying conflict</li>
					<li>May lack sufficient sense of urgency</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Evaluating Performance</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table3">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Views performance appraisals as a means of teaching, not admonishing </li>
					<li>Perceives the needs of people</li>
					<li>Effectively links needs of people to the organization’s needs</li>
					<li>Allows employees to draw their own conclusions based on evaluation</li>
					<li>Sincerely seeks to serve people</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>May be selfish with information</li>
					<li>Personal turf may be too important</li>
					<li>May be too lenient with mediocre performers</li>
					<li>Over-relies on trusted associates</li>
					<li>Depends too heavily on the “tried and true”</li>
					<li>May not make the tough decisions fast enough</li>
					<li>May fall victim to “haloing”</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Conducting Development Review Session/Strategies</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table4">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Motivates others with sincerity</li>
					<li>Creates a non-threatening environment</li>
					<li>Makes people feel like “winners”</li>
					<li>Takes time with people to make sure the evaluation is clear</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Lacks obvious enthusiasm</li>
					<li>Non-demonstrative</li>
					<li>Too patient about achieving results</li>
					<li>May not push for closure of goals</li>
					<li>May focus more on process than results—the <em>how</em> rather than the <em>what</em></li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>